radiographic_examinations.findings: Dependent bibasilar atelectasis, mild ground-glass opacities, hyperemia surrounding the gallbladder fossa at the site of prior cholecystectomy, small amount of residual fluid likely representing seroma, patent hepatic and portal veins, oral contrast passes through stomach and small bowel without extravasation, no retroperitoneal air or duodenal leak, normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenals, kidneys enhance symmetrically with right kidney in pelvic position, normal visualized portions of large bowel, tiny amount of free intraperitoneal air and some in the abdominal wall consistent with recent open cholecystectomy, atherosclerotic calcifications throughout the descending aorta.
